                      <td width="542" height="3019" colspan="3" valign="top" align="left" xpos="12"> 

                        <table cool width="542" height="698" showgridx showgridy gridx="8" gridy="8" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">

                          <tr height="47"> <!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="titleauthor" --> 

                            <td height="81" colspan="5" align="left" xpos="0" content valign="top" csheight="40"><b><font size="+1" face="Arial,Helvetica,Geneva,Swiss,SunSans-Regular" color="white">Closer</font></b><br>

                              <font face="Arial,Helvetica,Geneva,Swiss,SunSans-Regular" size="+1" color="maroon"><b>by 

                              Kathryn Stripling Byer</b></font> 

                              <p></p>

                              <spacer type="block" width="1" height="47"></td>

                            <!-- InstanceEndEditable --></tr>

                          <tr height="2831"> 

                            <td width="36" height="382"></td>

                            <!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="content" -->

                            <td height="382" colspan="4" align="left" xpos="20" content valign="top" csheight="2831"> 

                              <pre><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="3">

old road dreaming me back home

through coastal plain into the Gulf



stunted pines along the roadside

dripping with dark into night puddles 



arcade of pecan trees into infinity

through which my memory roams



like spider webs over wounds

these bare branches over my eyes



maybe souls do flow into and out of the world--

that crow over corn stubble, scythe of light



off the truck's chrome, swish of an icy 

mare's tail over the December sky

</font></pre></td>

