                                    <div align="left"> 

                                      <p><i><font color="maroon"><b><a href="mailto:Ksbyer@aol.com">Kathryn 

                                        Stripling Byer</a></b> lives in the mountains 

                                        of western North Carolina. She has published 

                                        four books of poetry, including </font></i><font color="maroon">Wildwood 

                                        Flower<i> (LSU) which was the 1992 Lamont 

                                        Selection of the Academy of American Poets. 

                                        Her latest is</i> Catching Light<i>, (LSU), 

                                        a 2002 </i>L.A. Times<i> Book Award nominee. 

                                        A chapbook, </i>Wake<i>, is due from Spring 

                                        Street Editions in March. </i></font></p>

